\begin_body

\begin_layout Chapter
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This chapter introduces the product to the reader and is called the 
\emph on
product brief
\emph default
.
 It contains the following sections.
 The questions raised in the following sections are representative of a
 generic product.
 These questions need to be addressed through the contents written in this
 chapter.
 It should be noted that the questions are not exhaustive.
 If however, you feel that the questions do not address a specific need
 for your product, then do not hesitate to address them too.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Background
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Give the motivation and need with figures and block diagrams to explain
 your project.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Functional aspects
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following questions need to be addressed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the primary function of the proposed product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What are the secondary functions if any?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Does a similar product exsit in the market?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Does the product form a part of a bigger system or should it work in conjuction
 with other equipments?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Are there any standards or protocols that need to be followed?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Characteristics and performance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following questions need to be addressed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What are the parameters to be measured, monitored and controlled by the
 product or product system?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What are the performance requirements that is expected of the product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Are there any absolute maximum ratings on any of the input or output parameters?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Which are the variables that are likely to influence the performance of
 the product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Are there any special considerations about the input and/or output signals?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
User aspects
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following questions need to be addressed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the technical competence of the user?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Is there any constant user-product interaction required?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What are the ergonomical constraints brought in by the usage pattern?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Is the product operated continuously or intermittently?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What will be the specific documentation of the product that is required
 by the user?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Is the user required to perform installation and maintenance?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Environment aspects
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following questions need to be addressed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
How do you classify the application of the product from the environmental
 point of view? (
\emph on
Refer to MIL-STD for environmental classifications on the web
\emph default
)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the ambient temperature range in the neighbourhood of the product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Do humidity, vibration and pressure affect the operation and design of the
 product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What other environmental parameters have significant impact on the product
 operation?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Power supply
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following questions need to be addressed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is the product battery operated?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What will be the effect of a power breakdown on the product or the associated
 system?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Are there special considerations or limitations on the power consumption
 of the product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Safety
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following questions need to be addressed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In case of supply voltages upto 270V with respect to earth, what is the
 nature of the location in which the equipment is to be installed?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the class of the product from the point of view of the safety standards?
 (
\emph on
refer to web
\emph default
)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Reliability
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following questions need to be addressed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the warranty/gaurantee conditions that will be proposed for your
 product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the targeted reliability figure in terms of MTTF(mean time to failure)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the proposed service infrastructure for the product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What should be the operational downtime to uptime ratio for the product?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the targeted maintainability figure in terms of MTTR(mean time to
 repair)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Wish scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following questions need to be addressed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the scope of the product that you wish to undertake?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the set of dream/wish specifications that you consider would be
 ideal for your product?
\end_layout

\end_body
\end_document
